review 1: the place is very nice. the property is in a small forest between the planting of rice, and a River of crystal-clear waters and clean. it has many species of birds and you don't have the mosquito, and well, monkeys. The access to the beaches and is close to passing through the small villages and farms. It is one of Bali's fifty-year-old in the back. a great place to meditate and do yoga, with a Max.
review 2: Secret villa in the jungle of Medewi, beautiful and peaceful environment. No mostquitoes with a private river and an amazing view of rice terraces and the ocean. The owner offers yoga classes, acroyoga, surf classes and guide and a lot of hospitality.
review 3:
Very quiet place in jungle with a hospitable host.
fresh air, rice fields all around and the lack of tourists makes this place truly attractive for practicing yoga and surfing
